1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. g3 Bb4+ 5. Nc3 O-O 6. Bg2 dxc4 7. O-O Nc6 8. Qa4 { This is White's 2nd choice by statistics. The active queen puts presure on Black's queenside setup, especially c4-pawn. In particular, a2-a3 is more effective from now. } 8... Nd5 { Avoiding the pin and intending to secure the c4-pawn with ... Nd5-b6 or ...b7-b5. } ( { The attempt to claim drawbacks of White's last move by means of } 8... Bd7 { meets } 9. Bg5 $1 Bxc3 10. bxc3 Nxd4 11. Qxc4 Nc6 12. Rfd1 { White had interesting compensation for the pawn in Roiz,M - Psakhis, L Israel 2018 } ) 9. Qc2 Be7 { The bishop did its job on b4, and now Black moves it back to vacate b4 for one of his knights. } 10. Rd1 { White streghtens d4 and places his rook in opposite to Black's queen. Potentially, it will yield White some extra resourses such as ..Nf3-e5. } ( { Premature is } 10. e4 Ndb4 11. Qd1 Nd3 $15 { Khusnutdinov,R - Hambleton,A Chess.com INT 2021 } ) 10... Rb8 11. e4 { A conceptual continuation. White takes the upper hand in the centre. } ( { The pseudo-aggressive } 11. h4 $6 b5 12. Ng5 { Ponkratov,P - Potkin,V Sochi 2021 runs into } 12... f5 $1 13. b3 Bf6 14. Nxd5 exd5 $17 { White is almost lost from strategic point of view. } ) ( 11. Ne5 Nxe5 12. dxe5 c6 13. Ne4 { took place in Prohaszka,P - Bok,B Saint Louis 2018 In my opinion, Black shouldn't devite from the most natural } 13... b5 $14 14. b3 Ba6 15. Bb2 Qc7 { White struggles to claim sufficient compensation for the pawn. } ) ( { Even worse is } 11. Ne4 $6 b5 12. Neg5 f5 $17 { Karpov,A - Piket,J Monte Carlo 1994 } ) 11... Ncb4 { Black's knight is heading on d3 in order to claim drawbacks of e2-e4. } ( { In my opinion, after } 11... Ndb4 12. Qe2 Nd3 13. Be3 $44 { White has full compensation and decent prospects in the centre. } ) 12. Qd2 { A somewhat awkward retreat because the c1-bishop is blocked. Still, it is White's top choice. } ( { The alternatives are: } 12. Qb1 Nxc3 13. bxc3 Nd3 14. Qb5 { White regains the pawn at cost of concessing his important bishop. } 14... Nxc1 15. Raxc1 c5 $1 { Black doesn't hesitate and start shooting the enemy center. } 16. Qxc4 ( { Equally possible is } 16. Ne5 a6 17. Qxc4 b5 18. Qe2 Qc7 { Black had a comfortable play in Salzmann,S - Esin, M LSS email 2019 } ) 16... b5 { The most active response - Black grabs space and signals that he intents to make a passer. } 17. Qe2 Qc7 18. c4 { This is the only challenging idea - White is trying to take advantage of favorable opposition on the c-file. } 18... bxc4 ( 18... b4 $5 { is another interesting options. } ) 19. Qxc4 Bd7 { Black manages to fully consolidate. } 20. dxc5 Rfc8 21. Qd4 Be8 { Black regains the pawn and maintains all his merits. Goltseva,E - Kamalidenova, M Cala Gonone 2022 } ) ( { and } 12. Qe2 Nxc3 13. bxc3 Nd3 14. a4 { we have been following th game Chigaev,M - Svane,R Chess.com INT 2022In my opinion, Black should have strenghtened his most active pieces by means of } ( { After } 14. Ne5 Nxe5 15. dxe5 Bd7 { Black has a better pawn structure. White's hopes are connected solely with attack on the k-side, but it doesn't seem to work. For instance, } 16. a4 c5 17. Qg4 Kh8 18. f4 { This was Yanayt,E - Arvind,C Ledyard 2019 Black could have claimed superiority by means of } 18... Qa5 $14 19. Rxd7 Qxc3 { White loses a piece in unfavorable situation: } 20. Rb1 Qc2 21. Ra1 Rbd8 $17 ) 14... b6 $14 15. Ne1 { , and then after most probable } 15... Ba6 16. Nxd3 cxd3 17. Qg4 f5 $15 { White doesn't seem to have proper compensation for the pawn. } ) 12... Nxc3 13. Qxc3 b5 14. b3 { White is aiming to unblock the c-file to put pressure on c7. } ( { Pointless is } 14. Ne1 { Stocek,J - Navara,D Usti nad Labem 2022 } 14... Nc6 $14 15. Nc2 a5 16. b3 Ba6 $15 ) ( 14. a4 { , as in Lenaerts,L - Esipenko,A Tornelo INT 2021 meets } 14... Bb7 $14 15. axb5 Bxe4 16. Qxc4 Qd5 $15 { White has to struggle for equality as his pawn structure in inferior. } ) 14... Bb7 15. Ne1 { White builds on a long-term pressure on the queenside. } ( { After } 15. a3 Nd3 16. bxc4 Nxc1 17. Raxc1 Bxe4 { Black had excellent play due to bishop pair in Juksta,K - Antipov,M Reykjavik 2021 } ) 15... cxb3 16. axb3 f5 $5 { The most energetic - Black doesn't mind to give the pawn back in order to undermine opponent's pawn centre. } ( { Quieter is } 16... a6 17. Bb2 f6 18. h4 $44 ) 17. exf5 Bxg2 18. Nxg2 Rxf5 19. Rxa7 ( { After } 19. Ne3 Nd5 20. Qc2 Nxe3 21. fxe3 Rf7 22. Rxa7 Bd6 $15 { White's king got in danger in Naiditsch,A - Huschenbeth,N Khanty-Mansiysk 2019 } ) 19... Bd6 20. Qe1 Qd7 { Black had decent play on the light squares in Lopez Gonzalez,A - Avila Rodriguez,J Mexico City 2022 } *
