1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. g3 Bb4+ 5. Nbd2 dxc4 ( 5... O-O 6. Bg2 b6 7. O-O Bb7 { is a solid alternative, that leads to long positional play, when Black has to accept either handing pawns or IQP. } ) 6. Bg2 b5 7. a3 ( 7. a4 { This move mostly meets 7...c6, as was played in major high-level games. However, in this redaction Black has another attractive option. } 7... c3 $5 8. bxc3 Bxc3 9. Rb1 { This was played in all the games so far. } ( { Possibly, stronger is } 9. Ra2 $5 { , as hasn't been tried yet. A likely scenario is } 9... Bb7 10. axb5 O-O 11. O-O Bxd4 12. Ba3 Re8 13. Nc4 Bb6 $11 { Activity of pieces provides White sufficient compensation for the pawn, but not more. } ) 9... b4 10. Ne5 ( 10. O-O Bb7 { leaves White no compensation for the pawn. } ) 10... Nd5 { A standard way of blocking the long diagonal. } 11. O-O { This was Rotstein,A - Trella,T Germany 2009 Black could have grabed another pawn: } 11... Bxd4 $14 12. Ndf3 Bxe5 13. Nxe5 a5 $1 { Black strengtens b4 and prevents ..Rxb4. } 14. Bb2 ( { The endgame, that arises after } 14. e4 $2 Nc3 15. Qxd8+ Kxd8 16. Nxf7+ Ke8 17. Nxh8 Nxb1 $19 { is absolutely hopeless for White. } ) 14... O-O 15. Qd4 f6 16. Rfd1 c6 $15 { White has no sufficient compensation for 2 pawns. } ) ( 7. Ne5 Nd5 8. O-O O-O { transposes to 7.0-0. } ) 7... Be7 8. b3 { White is interested in exchanging the c4-pawn to activate the pieces. } ( 8. Ne5 Nd5 9. O-O Bb7 10. a4 c6 { This allows Black to maintain his extra pawn. } ( { The natural } 10... a6 { runs into } 11. axb5 axb5 12. Rxa8 Bxa8 13. Ndxc4 $1 { White regains the pawn in favorable situation because 13...bxc4 is met by 14. Qa4+. Makarian,R - Dudin,G Arandjelovac 2021 } ) 11. e4 Nf6 12. Ndf3 O-O 13. Ng5 $14 { This innovation seems critical. White insists pressure on the kingside. } ( { The previously played } 13. Qe2 $6 { is too slow: } 13... Nbd7 14. Rd1 a6 15. g4 Nxe5 16. Nxe5 Nd7 { Black's chances were much were much better in Chigaev,M - Bluebaum,M Chess.com INT 2022 } ) 13... Qe8 $1 { It is very important to strenghten f7. } 14. f4 Nbd7 15. Nexf7 { White has to go all in. The situation is getting very sharp. } 15... Rxf7 16. Nxe6 Bd8 $1 { A decent consolidating move. } 17. f5 c5 18. d5 Ne5 { The strong e5-knight provides Black stability, so his extra piece prevails. } ) 8... cxb3 9. Qxb3 a6 { Defending the pawn and vacating a7 for the rook. } 10. Ne5 Ra7 11. Bb2 Nfd7 { The exchange of e5-knight will significantly ease Black's play. } 12. Nd3 ( { In the event of } 12. d5 Nxe5 13. Bxe5 O-O 14. Qe3 { Black manages to take over initiative by means of } 14... Nd7 $1 15. Qxa7 Nxe5 $36 { The a7-queen is misplaced, and bishop pair seems to play an important role. } ) 12... O-O 13. O-O Nb6 14. Rac1 { Natural play by both sides led to this position in Andreikin,D - Svane,R Chess.com INT 2021 Here I suggest the energetic } 14... Na4 $14 15. Ba1 Bb7 16. e4 Bf6 $15 { White is in trouble because his pawn centre is vulnerable and he is down a pawn. } *
