1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. g3 Bb4+ 5. Nbd2 dxc4 6. Bg2 b5 7. O-O { A top choice by far. White castles and unpins his knight. } 7... O-O ( 7... Bb7 { is somewhat inaccurate as it allows } 8. Nxc4 bxc4 9. Qa4+ Nc6 10. Ne5 { , and White gets the pawn back in favorable redaction. } ) ( 7... a5 $5 { is another interesting option. } ) 8. Ne5 { The most common alternative to 8.a4. White activates his knight and unblocks the finachettoes bishop. } ( 8. Ne1 c6 9. Nc2 { makes a little sense as 9...a5 is a useful move anyways. } ( 9. a4 { transposes to 8.a4. } ) 9... a5 10. a4 Ra6 { Black moves his rook away from dangerous diagonal and streghtens c6. } 11. e4 Nbd7 12. e5 { White grabs lots of space and activates his dark-squared bishop. } ( 12. Qe2 { is met by } 12... e5 $1 13. Nf3 exd4 14. Ncxd4 Ne5 $17 { Black solves all his issues with development and maintains the extra pawn. } ) 12... Nd5 13. Ne4 Be7 14. Qg4 f5 $17 { White's attack was fully neutralized, so Black has decent chances for converting hi extra pawn. Papaioannou,I - Vidit,S Vrachati 2013 } ) ( { The other possibilities are: } 8. a3 Be7 9. Ne5 ( { In the event of } 9. b3 { the simplest way to solve the problems seems } 9... Bb7 $5 ( { Instead, } 9... cxb3 10. Qxb3 a6 11. a4 b4 12. Ne5 Ra7 13. Ndc4 $44 { provides White long-term compensation for the pawn in view of awkward a7-rook in Tyulenko,Y - Keijzer,R ICCF email 2017 } ) 10. bxc4 bxc4 11. Rb1 ( { Harmless is also } 11. Nxc4 c5 12. dxc5 Nbd7 13. Nd6 Bd5 $11 { with ...Nxc5 to follow. } ) 11... Bd5 12. Qc2 c3 $1 { Black gives the pawn back to diminish White's control of e4. } 13. Qxc3 Nbd7 14. Ne5 { The most challenging move - White's knight is heading on c6. } ( { After } 14. Qc2 Rc8 15. e4 Ba8 16. e5 Nd5 $15 { Black took the upper hand in Filip,L - Chiriac,D Iasi 2023 } ) 14... Bxg2 15. Kxg2 c5 { This break comes on time. } 16. Nc6 cxd4 17. Qxd4 Bc5 $11 { Black manages to fully solve all his issues. } ) ( { Weaker is } 9. a4 c6 10. Qc2 Na6 $1 { An energetic response. It turns out, that c2-queen is vulnerable. } 11. b3 Nb4 12. Qb2 Ba6 13. axb5 ( 13. Ne5 Nfd5 $17 ) 13... cxb5 14. Ne5 Rc8 $15 { Black is still up a pawn, when his queenside development is completed. } ) 9... c6 10. Bxc6 { A big concession, although White manages to damage Black's pawn chain. } ( { For some reason, the dubious } 10. a4 $6 { was played in the major of games } 10... Nd5 11. e4 Nb4 12. d5 { This is the only reasonable try - White has to go all in! } 12... Qc7 13. Nxc6 N8xc6 14. dxc6 Ba6 $17 { White was positionally busted in Aditya,V - Kojima,S Budapest 2021 } ) ( 10. Nxc6 $6 Nxc6 11. Bxc6 Rb8 { leaves White in passive position, when Black's pawn majority prevails. } ) 10... Nxc6 11. Nxc6 Qc7 12. Nxe7+ Qxe7 { White's king feels unsafe from now. } 13. a4 { The only reasonable idea - White separates opponent's queenside pawns. } 13... Bb7 14. axb5 Qd7 { Of coursem, the c4-pawn is intouchable in view of ...Qd5. } 15. e3 Qxb5 { Black had nothing to worry about in Tunega,F - Halliwell,T ICCF email 2017 } ) ( { Another try is somewhat akward: } 8. b3 c3 9. Nb1 { White wastes few tempi to regain the pawn. } 9... Bb7 10. a3 Be4 11. Qe1 ( { Dubious is } 11. Ne1 $6 Bxg2 12. Kxg2 Ba5 13. b4 Bb6 14. e3 a5 $17 { Dylag,E - Sarkar,J Prague 2022 } ) 11... c2 12. Nc3 Bxc3 13. Qxc3 Nc6 { Black develops his minor pieces most actively. } 14. Bb2 a5 15. Rfc1 b4 { White had to struggle for equality in Makhnev,D - Sarana,A Porto Carras 2018 } ) 8... Nd5 9. Qc2 { White is aiming to connect his rooks. } ( { Premature is } 9. e4 $2 Nb6 { White has no comfortable way to cover d4. } 10. Ndf3 Bb7 11. Qe2 a5 $17 { Dylag,E - Johnson,B Chess.com INT 2022 } ) ( 9. b3 Bb7 10. bxc4 { meets } ( 10. Qc2 { transposes to 9.Qc2. } ) 10... Nc3 11. Qe1 { The only retreat. Now White' heavy pieces are misplaced. } 11... Bxg2 12. Kxg2 Ne4 13. e3 bxc4 { Black has excellent piece play. } ) ( 9. a3 Be7 10. b3 { was recently tried by few strong players. } 10... Bb7 ( { In case of } 10... cxb3 11. Qxb3 a6 12. Qc2 { White maintains interesting play for the pawn, and 13.Nb3 is to follow. } ) 11. bxc4 Nc3 { The knight is unstable, but it interrupts White's piece coordination. } 12. Qe1 Bxg2 13. Kxg2 bxc4 14. Ndxc4 ( 14. Ndf3 Ne4 15. Nxc4 Qd5 16. Ne3 Qb7 { was comfortable for Black in Robson,R - Caruana,F Saint Louis 2022 } ) 14... Qxd4 15. Be3 Qd5+ 16. f3 Na4 { Black has a solid position. White definitely has compensation for the pawn, but it will only suffice for equality. Mikhalevski, V - Kozak,A Warsaw 2021 } ) 9... Bb7 10. b3 { This gambit idea was seen in a couple of games of DB Dubov, who can be considered as one of leading Catalan experts. } 10... Bc3 { The most forcing. } ( { Somewhat passive is } 10... cxb3 11. Nxb3 a5 12. Rd1 Qe7 13. Nd3 { Black got under pressure in Dubov,D - Bluebaum,M Chess. com INT 2022 } ) 11. Rb1 Bxd4 12. bxc4 Bxe5 13. cxd5 Bxd5 14. e4 { The most ambitious choice. White is aiming to interrupt Black's natural development. } ( { After } 14. Rxb5 Bxg2 15. Kxg2 { activity of pieces provides White full compensation for the pawn. A likely scenario is } 15... Nd7 16. Nf3 Bf6 17. Ba3 { This was Dubov,D - Bok,B Chess.com INT 2022 Now Black should have played } 17... c5 $14 18. Rb7 Qc8 19. Qe4 h6 { White will most likely regain the pawn, but it will not yield him any advantage. } ) 14... Bc6 15. Rd1 ( { Equally possible is } 15. Nf3 Bd6 16. Nd4 Qd7 17. Be3 b4 $1 { Black reasonably builds counterplay on his pawn majority. } 18. Nxc6 Nxc6 19. Rbc1 Ne5 { it is crucial to temporarily block the e-pawn. White has definite compensation for 2 pawns, but it is only enough for maintaining the balance. A likely continuation is } 20. Qe2 Be7 21. Rfd1 Qa4 22. f4 Ng6 23. Rxc7 Rfc8 { Black has no problems. } ) 15... Qe8 16. Nf3 Bd6 17. Nd4 { Henderson de la Fuente,L - Cuenca Jimenez,J Mexico City 2022 Here my new natural idea is } 17... b4 $14 { White has nothing better than forcing the matters: } 18. e5 Bxg2 19. exd6 Bd5 20. dxc7 { White has a powerful c7-passer, but Black is up a pawn, and his light-squared bishop is very strong. } 20... Na6 21. Bf4 Qd7 22. Rbc1 Rac8 { The c7-passer is currently blocked. The chances are mutual. } *
