1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. g3 Bb4+ 5. Bd2 a5 6. Bg2 O-O 7. Qc2 c5 8. O-O { This is the most common among White's side options. Black is invited to show his cards. } ( 8. Bxb4 axb4 9. dxc5 d4 { transposes to 8.dxc5. } ) ( 8. a3 { A rare move. } 8... Bxd2+ 9. Nbxd2 ( 9. Qxd2 { , as in Wu,B - Liyanage,R Almaty 2023 meets } 9... dxc4 $14 10. O-O { White builds his play on pressure along h1-a8 diagonal, as in most of Catalan lines. Being a pawn down isn't a big issue. } ( { After } 10. dxc5 Nbd7 11. Nc3 Nxc5 12. Qxd8 Rxd8 13. Ne5 Rb8 14. Nxc4 b6 $11 { Black has nothing to worry about. } ) 10... Nbd7 11. Nc3 b6 $1 { The simplest way - Black only needs to move his bishop in order to fully solve the problems. } 12. Ne5 Nxe5 13. Bxa8 cxd4 { Black has 2 pawns for an exchange, and the a8-bishop is misplaced. } 14. Rfd1 d3 15. Bg2 Ba6 $13 { In this unbalanced position Black's chances are not worse. } ) 9... cxd4 10. Nxd4 e5 { Black uses the fact, that d2-knight isn't active enough. } 11. Nb5 Bd7 12. a4 { This position occured in Pashikian,A -Ter Sahakyan,S Yerevan 2021 Here I suggest the following healthy approach: } 12... Be6 $14 13. cxd5 Nxd5 14. Rd1 Nc6 15. O-O Qe7 $11 { Black has fully consolidated. } ) 8... cxd4 9. Nxd4 Nc6 { Now White should either strenghten Black's centre or waste a tempo by retreating his knight. } ( 9... e5 $5 { also scores well on practice. } ) 10. Nxc6 ( { The most reasonable way to retreat the knight is } 10. Nb5 Qb6 11. a3 $14 ( { Dubious is } 11. Be3 $6 d4 12. Bg5 Be7 $15 { Toniutti,E - Horvath,D Chess.com INT 2022 } ) 11... Bxd2 12. Nxd2 Ne5 $1 { Activating the knight and making ... Bc8-d7 more attractive. } 13. a4 Nxc4 14. Nxc4 dxc4 15. Qxc4 Bd7 $11 { White has no advantage. } ) ( 10. Bc3 { , as in Xiong,J - Matlakov,M Chess.com INT 2020 can be simply met by } 10... Bxc3 $14 11. Qxc3 Qb6 12. Rd1 Bd7 13. cxd5 Nxd5 $11 { with a full equality. } ) 10... bxc6 11. Rd1 ( { Weaker is } 11. a3 $6 Bd6 12. Nc3 Ba6 { This is the point - White's queenside setup is more vulnerable now. } 13. cxd5 cxd5 $15 { Strybuk,A - Vokhidov,S Chess.com INT 2021 } ) 11... Ba6 12. b3 { Natural play by both sides led to this position in Botsari,A - Lei,T Chess.com INT 2021 Here I like the following way of handling the position: } 12... Qe7 $14 13. Nc3 Rfd8 14. Na4 { Now Black has few interesting possibilities, such as } 14... Bxd2 15. Rxd2 dxc4 16. bxc4 Qb4 $11 { Black has no problems. } *
