1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. g3 Bb4+ 5. Bd2 a5 6. Bg2 O-O 7. Qc2 c5 8. cxd5 { White is traditionally aiming to create and isolated d5-pawn. } 8... cxd4 9. Nxd4 { The most natural and common by far. } ( { The other possibilities are: } 9. Bxb4 axb4 { this yeilds Black lots of play along the a-file. } 10. Nxd4 Qb6 11. e3 ( { After } 11. Nb3 exd5 12. O-O Nc6 13. N1d2 Bg4 14. Nf3 Rfc8 15. Qd3 Bh5 { Black's active piece play fully compensated for IQP in Ryjanova,J - Alinasab,M Baku 2023 } ) 11... exd5 12. Nd2 Nc6 13. N2b3 Bg4 { The most active way of development. Now c8 is vacant for the rooks. } 14. O-O Rfc8 15. Qd2 Ne5 $13 { It is hard to prevent 16...Nc4. Black has enough counterplay against opponent's queenside pawns. Dragomirescu,A - Voiska,M Borovetz 2008 } ) ( 9. dxe6 { This assits Black in activating his minor pieces. } 9... Bxe6 10. O-O Nc6 11. Bxb4 { This position occured in Ochs,D - Baselmans,L Wachtebeke 2023 Here I suggest } 11... Nxb4 $14 12. Qd2 d3 { The most straightforward. } 13. exd3 Bxa2 14. Nc3 Be6 { Black has excellent play due to superior pawn structure. } ) ( 9. a3 Bxd2+ 10. Qxd2 Qxd5 { Black reasonably opts for symmetrical pawn structure. } ( { Less attractive is } 10... exd5 11. Nxd4 Ne4 12. Bxe4 $1 dxe4 13. Nc3 { Vulnerablity of e4-pawn made Black's position unpleasant in Visakh,N - Sargsyan,S Biel 2022 } ) 11. Qxd4 Nc6 12. Qxd5 Nxd5 13. Nbd2 ( { Also after } 13. O-O Rd8 14. Rd1 Bd7 15. Nbd2 Be8 { Black reaches a harmonious setup. A likely continuation is } 16. Rac1 Kf8 17. Nc4 b5 18. Nce5 Nxe5 19. Nxe5 Rac8 { with full equality. } ) 13... Rd8 14. O-O b6 { Both b7 and a6 are now vacant for the bishop. } ( 14... Bd7 $5 { should also suffice for equality. } ) 15. Rac1 ( { I also examined: } 15. Nc4 Ba6 16. Rfc1 Rab8 { Black covers his only weak spot. } 17. Nce5 Nxe5 18. Nxe5 Bb5 19. f4 Kf8 $11 ) 15... Bb7 16. Rfd1 Rac8 17. Nc4 b5 $1 { A well-timed advance. Black can with weakening c5. } 18. Nce5 Nxe5 19. Nxe5 Kf8 20. Nd3 { Hardly White has other attractive plans at his disposal. } 20... Ke7 21. Nc5 Ba8 $11 { Black didn't have any problems in Wojtaszek,R -Le,Q chess24.com INT 2022 } ) 9... Qb6 $1 { By playing this m voe Black claims some drawbacks of opponent's setup. } 10. Nf3 { A common alternative to main 10.e3. } ( 10. a3 { can be well met by } 10... Bc5 $1 11. e3 Bxd4 12. exd4 Nxd5 { White's bishop pair is fully compensated by strong blockading d5-knight. } 13. Nc3 Nc6 14. Nxd5 exd5 15. Be3 Be6 $11 { Black had no problems in Sviridov,V - Badelka,O Dubai 2023 } ) 10... exd5 11. O-O Bxd2 { 11...Nc6 is a considerable alternative that was seen in majot of games. However, I prefer to exchange bishops an eliminate some ideas such as ..Bd2-e3 or Bd2-g5. } 12. Nbxd2 ( { Another natural possibility is } 12. Qxd2 { This move hasn't been tried, but it makes sense to develop the knight more actively. } 12... Nc6 13. Nc3 Bg4 { Black also opts for the most active way of development. } 14. h3 ( { In case of } 14. Rfd1 Rfe8 15. Nd4 Nxd4 16. Qxd4 Qxd4 17. Rxd4 Bxe2 { White will regain the pawn, but it will only yield him equality. } ) 14... Bxf3 15. Bxf3 ( { After } 15. exf3 d4 16. Na4 Qb5 17. b3 Rad8 { Black has a sufficient counterplay due to his strong passer. } ) 15... Rad8 16. Rfd1 ( { The ''greedy'' } 16. Nxd5 $6 Nxd5 17. Bxd5 Nd4 { puts White in danger in view of pin. } ) 16... d4 17. Ne4 Nxe4 18. Bxe4 Rfe8 $11 { pressure on e2 and active piece play fully compensates for White's strong bishop. } ) 12... Nc6 13. Rac1 { This position took place in a couple of GM's games.Here my natural new idea is } ( { Toothless is } 13. Rfc1 a4 14. a3 { Tabatabaei,M - Sychev,K Chess.com INT 2023 } 14... Be6 15. Rab1 Rfc8 $11 ) ( { Or } 13. Qb3 Ra6 { Black activates his rook before trading queens. } 14. Qxb6 Rxb6 $11 { Postny,E - Filippov,A Sibenik 2012 } ) 13... a4 $14 { Black grabs space and deprives White's knight of b3. } 14. e3 { White strenghtens d4. } ( { Equally possible is } 14. Qc5 Qxc5 15. Rxc5 a3 $11 ) 14... h6 { A useful move - Black makes space for his king and secures e6 for the bishop. } 15. Qc5 Qxc5 16. Rxc5 a3 $11 { Activity on the a file enables Black to solve all his problems. } *

