{ [#]Quite a typical situation for the Catalan. White has gambited the c4-pawn and was able to build a strong pawn center. Now he wants to play Rad1 and start playing in the center. We will have a look at some possibilities of how to handle such a position from the black side. } 11... Ng4 $5 { There is a very concrete idea connected to this move. } ( 11... Bb7 { Black can also handle the position in this more restrained manner. } 12. Rad1 Na5 { Stepping out of the d4-d5 advance and heading for b3. } 13. d5 Qe8 $5 ( { Exchanging pawn might seem more natural but is less precise because it opens the e-file and weakens square f5 which may be used by the f3-knight. } 13... exd5 14. exd5 Nb3 { (otherwise Nd4 might be unpleasant) } 15. a4 { offers White enough compensation. } ) 14. Bh3 { White wants to provoke an exchange on d5 in order to open the e-file. } ( 14. dxe6 fxe6 { is not to be feared as Black profits from the opening of the f-file and the diagonal e8-h5 for his queen. } 15. Ng5 $6 { backfires after } 15... Ng4 $1 16. Nxe6 Qh5 17. h4 Nxe3 18. fxe3 Rxf1+ 19. Rxf1 Qe5 $17 { White's position is a sorry sight. } ) 14... Nb3 $5 { Black doesn't need to comply as after } 15. dxe6 fxe6 16. Bxe6+ Kh8 { he would have the better game with ideas like ...Qh5 or ...Bd6. Black's pieces work together very harmoniously. } ) 12. Bf4 g5 $1 { This is the point of 11...Ng4. Black weakens his king, but forces White to part with his important black-squared bishop. } ( { In case of } 12... Nxd4 13. Nxd4 Qxd4 14. e5 $44 { White has promising compensation for the two pawns due to his advantage in development and the insecure position of Black's pieces, e.g. } 14... Rb8 ( 14... Qa7 $13 ) 15. Qe2 Nh6 16. Rad1 Qb6 17. Be3 $5 c5 18. Bxh6 gxh6 19. Ne4 $36 ) 13. Be3 Nxe3 14. fxe3 g4 15. Nh4 { This position occurred in Theodorou,N - Samaridis,K Paleochora 2019. } 15... e5 $14 { Locking in the g2-bishop and fixing the center. } 16. Nf5 Kh8 17. Rad1 Bd6 $1 { Blocking the d-file and clearing the diagonal d8-h4 for d8-queen. } 18. Qf2 Qg5 $13 { Black's chances are by no means worse. } *
