{ [#]A position characteristic for the closed Catalan. We will highlight the principled opportunity to fight for the initiative with White and show the best defensive method for Black. } 12. Ne5 { The most important line. } ( 12. Nc3 Ba6 13. Ne5 Nxe5 ( 13... Rc8 $5 { is a good alternative. } ) 14. dxe5 Nd7 { leads to a transposition. } ) ( 12. Nbd2 { Here the knight gets in the way of the dark-squared bishop, for example } 12... Ba6 ( { The immediate } 12... g5 $6 { isn't convincing as Black fails to exchange the f4-bishop due to } 13. cxd5 $1 cxd5 ( { It is risky to take the piece as } 13... gxf4 14. dxc6 Qc7 15. Rac1 Nb8 16. Ne5 { gives White more than enough compensation. } ) 14. Bc7 $14 ) ( 12... Nh5 $5 { can be considered. } 13. Be5 $5 ( 13. Be3 $6 { Blocking the e-pawn deprives White of e2-e4. } 13... Ba6 $13 { [%cal Ya8c8] } ) 13... Bb7 $13 ) 13. e4 { can be met by } 13... g5 $5 14. Be3 Ng4 $13 { when gaining the pair of bishops offsets the weakening of Black's kingside. } ) 12... Nxe5 ( 12... Bb7 $6 13. Nc3 Rc8 $6 { Is too passive. Now White advances in the center and gets a clear advantage. } 14. e4 $16 ) 13. dxe5 Nd7 14. Nc3 ( 14. cxd5 cxd5 15. e4 d4 $1 16. Rxd4 Bc5 17. Rd1 g5 { leads to a transposition after } 18. Bc1 Ba6 19. Nc3 Rc8 ) 14... Ba6 $14 { The most active square for the queen's bishop. } 15. cxd5 cxd5 16. e4 { We have arrived at the critical moment. } 16... d4 $1 { Black must sacrifice a pawn to keep the g2-bishop out of play and to avoid giving the beautiful e4-square to the knight on c3. } ( 16... dxe4 $2 17. Nxe4 $16 ) 17. Rxd4 Bc5 18. Rdd1 ( { The other retreat } 18. Rd2 { looks more logical, but after } 18... g5 19. Rad1 Bc8 $1 { it turns out, that White has nothing better than } 20. Be3 Bxe3 21. fxe3 Qc7 $15 { when Black's structural superiority offers more than enough compensation for the missing pawn. } ) 18... g5 19. Bc1 Rc8 $1 { Black has time to activate the rook because White cannot move his f2-pawn yet. } ( { The immediate } 19... Qe7 20. Na4 $1 { lets White exchange Black's powerful bishop. } ) 20. Kh1 Qe7 { Connecting the rooks and unpinning the knight. } 21. f4 f6 $5 ( { The more restrained } 21... Rfd8 $44 { is also possible. } ) 22. exf6 Nxf6 $44 { Black's pieces are much better mobilized, and this fully compensates for the missing pawn. } *
